\chapter{Virtual Environments}

Recent Python distributions increasingly follow PEP~668 and reject direct
[[pip install]] commands into the system interpreter.  That is usually the
right default, but [[mentipy]] has one extra constraint: PythonTeX imports the
package from the same [[python3]] that builds the document.  A small helper
module therefore keeps the environment-preparation workflow explicit and
scriptable from both the CLI and user code.

